DayThem — Database Migrations (Alembic)
=======================================

Schema changes are managed with Alembic. The DB URL is read from
daythem.config.settings.DATABASE_URL (env var DATABASE_URL / .env), NOT from
alembic.ini, so the same commands work for sqlite (dev/tests) and PostgreSQL
(prod).

Run all commands from C:\DayThem\backend.

Apply all pending migrations (create/upgrade schema to latest):
    alembic upgrade head

Roll back the most recent migration:
    alembic downgrade -1

Show current DB revision / history:
    alembic current
    alembic history --verbose

Create a new migration after changing ORM models in
src/daythem/adapters/orm.py (review the generated file before committing):
    alembic revision --autogenerate -m "describe the change"

Generate SQL without touching a DB (offline mode):
    alembic upgrade head --sql

Notes
-----
- Tests and local dev still use create_tables() (Base.metadata.create_all) in
  src/daythem/adapters/database.py — that path is intentionally kept.
- For production, prefer `alembic upgrade head` over create_all so schema
  changes are versioned and reversible.
- Override the DB for a one-off run with an env var, e.g.:
      DATABASE_URL=sqlite:///./scratch.db alembic upgrade head
